# âœï¸ Git Amend â€” Detailed Notes

---

## 1ï¸âƒ£ What is `git commit --amend`?

`git commit --amend` ka matlab:

> **Last commit ko modify / update karna**
> (commit message change karna ya files add/remove karna)

ğŸ“Œ Ye **naya commit** banata hai
ğŸ“Œ Purane commit ko **replace** karta hai
ğŸ“Œ Commit hash **change ho jata hai**

---

## 2ï¸âƒ£ When to use Git Amend?

Use cases:

* Commit message me spelling mistake
* Koi file add karna bhool gaye
* Last commit me choti changes add karni hain
* Cleaner commit history chahiye

âŒ Use na karein:

* Jab commit already **shared / pushed** ho (unless force push allowed)

---

## 3ï¸âƒ£ Amend Commit Message Only

### Scenario:

Last commit message galat hai

```bash
git commit --amend
```

* Editor open hoga
* Message edit karo
* Save & close

ğŸ“Œ Code change nahi hota, sirf message

---

## 4ï¸âƒ£ Amend Commit with Files (Very Common)

### Scenario:

File change ki, lekin commit karna bhool gaye

```bash
git add missed-file.txt
git commit --amend
```

Result:

* File last commit ka hissa ban jaati hai
* Naya commit hash generate hota hai

---

## 5ï¸âƒ£ Amend Without Opening Editor

```bash
git commit --amend -m "Correct commit message"
```

---

## 6ï¸âƒ£ Amend Quickly (No Message Change)

```bash
git commit --amend --no-edit
```

ğŸ“Œ Jab sirf file add karni ho

---

## 7ï¸âƒ£ Internally kya hota hai? (IMPORTANT)

Before:

```
C1 â”€â”€â–º C2
```

After amend:

```
C1 â”€â”€â–º C2'
```

ğŸ“Œ `C2` delete nahi hota, lekin **unreachable** ho jata hai
ğŸ“Œ History rewrite hoti hai

---

## 8ï¸âƒ£ Amend + GitHub (Very Important Rule)

### Case 1: Commit NOT pushed

âœ… Safe

```bash
git commit --amend
```

### Case 2: Commit pushed to GitHub

âš ï¸ Dangerous unless allowed

```bash
git commit --amend
git push -f
```

ğŸ“Œ Force push sirf:

* Solo project
* Team ne allow kiya ho

---

## 9ï¸âƒ£ Common Beginner Mistakes

âŒ Amend after push without informing team
âŒ Force push on shared branch
âŒ Thinking amend creates extra commit (it does NOT)

---

## ğŸ”‘ Quick Cheat Sheet

| Task                     | Command                              |
| ------------------------ | ------------------------------------ |
| Edit last commit message | `git commit --amend`                 |
| Add file to last commit  | `git add file && git commit --amend` |
| Amend without editor     | `git commit --amend -m "msg"`        |
| Amend without msg change | `git commit --amend --no-edit`       |

---

## ğŸ§  Interview One-Liner

> "`git commit --amend` is used to modify the most recent commit by changing its message or content, rewriting commit history."

